# no-commit-projects.local — list of repo basenames whose project policy is /commit false.
#
# The baseline-stash hook (hooks/modules/15-baseline-stash.sh) reads this file
# at session start and auto-captures `git status` + `git diff` snapshots for any
# matching repo. These snapshots are injected into w-reviewer dispatch prompts so
# reviewers can distinguish pre-existing changes from the current wave's output
# (R-2 dirty-tree attribution mitigation).
#
# Format: one repo basename per line. Blank lines and lines starting with '#'
# are ignored. If this file is absent the hook is a safe no-op.
#
# Copy this file to no-commit-projects.local and add your repo basenames:
# my-webapp
# another-project
